ABEOKUTA – The immediate past Governor of Ogun State, Senator Ibikunle Amosun has denied any knowledge or involvement in an alleged smear campaign against his successor, Dapo Abiodun, telling him to explore legal means against perpetrators. The presidential aspirant under the umbrella of the All Progressives Congress, APC in a statement signed by his media aide, Bola, Adeyemi, a copy of which was sent to Independent, described the allegation as callous which must not be unaddressed. Amosun, the Senator representing Ogun Central at the National Assembly was reacting to a statement credited to Tunde Oladunjoye, though a publicity secretary of Ogun APC but issued the statement on behalf of Dapo Abiodun Campaign Organisation, titled “Fresh Attempt by Amosun to smear Gov Abiodun”. -Advertisement- In the statement, Oladunjoye alleged that Amosun’s loyalists have, recently, be coming up with malicious and false allegation to incriminate Abiodun, the allegations which Oladunjoye emphatically said were being sponsored by the former Governor. While reacting, Amosun said is was not involved either directly or indirectly on the alleged smear campaign challenging Abiodun to explore legal options. The statement read, “The attention of Senator Ibikunle Amosun has been drawn to a publication alleging that he was planning a smear campaign against the Governor of Ogun State, Mr Dapo Abiodun.” “Ordinarily, we do not respond to such wild accusations. However, this is one callous accusation that should not be allowed to pass unaddressed. “For the record, Sen Amosun is not involved, directly or indirectly, in any campaign against Governor Abiodun or any person for that matter. POLL “Sen Amosun implores Governor Abiodun to employ every legal means to bring whoever is involved in any such campaign against him, as alleged, to book.”